National_City.Bayside By Bosa: Bayside is the 14th tallest building in San Diego, California. Situated along the Embarcadero in the Core district of Downtown San Diego, Bayside is prominently located on the corner of Pacific Coast Highway and Ash Street on the waterfront's residential "front row." This 36-story (394 feet; 120m) building with its midnight blue and gold exterior contains 232 residences, including 208 tower suites, 12 town homes and 12 penthouses. Building features include a lobby with concierge, fitness center, library, lounge, pool/Jacuzzi w/outdoor kitchen, wine tasting room, and theater.
